cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.DL, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on building a retrieval system for a large archive of pictures of Buddha statues. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the system uses different CBIR (Content-Based Image Retrieval) techniques to analyze the images and extract facial characteristics of the statues. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the system combines 2D pictures, 3D scans, and meta-data to provide a comprehensive analysis of the statues. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is possible as the paper mentions the use of deep learning techniques for facial embedding. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also possible as the system provides 3D analysis and visualization of the statues.
